JDBC :- Java Database Connectivity or JDBC API provide industry standard and database independent connectivity b/w the java application and relational database servers.
	* Databases like MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL, Microsoft SQL, MangoDB.
	* JDBC allow a Java application to connect to a relational database.

java.sql :-
	Interfaces:-
		Driver
		Connection
		Statement
		PreparedStatement
		CallableStatement
		ResultSet
		ResultSetMetaData
		DataBaseMetaData
		
	Classes :-
		DriverManager
		Types
		Date
		Time
		
javax.sql :-
	Interfaces :-
		DataSource
		RowSet
	
	Classes :-
		RowSetEvent
		
Steps :-
	Resister the driver
	Creating connection
	Creating Statement
	Executing Queries
	Closing connection
	
Edition :-
	Enterprise edition
	Express Edition
